ents any valid (CA-signed) certificate for a different host.\n\n## Ranking / other candidates checked (all correct)\n\nI verified the other suspect areas and they all match upstream:\n- **CLIENT_AUTH_MAPPING** (lines 43-45): REQUIRED→REQUIRE, REQUEST→OPTIONAL, NONE→NONE — correct.\n- **`Config` constructor call** (line 234) vs declaration (line 296): argument order matches — no swap of key/trust mappers.\n- **`new SslContextProvider(...)`** (lines 161-173) vs constructor (lines 60-71): all positional arguments aligned correctly (hostnameVerificationAlgorithm→endpointIdentificationAlgorithm, cipher suites/protocols not swapped, key/trust managers and mappers in the right slots).\n- **`trustOptionsOf` / TrustAll** (lines 176-184): correct.\n- **`configureEngine`** `if (client)` block (lines 327-331): correct — endpoint identification is set on the client side, and the null→\"\" coercion itself is upstream behavior (it's only reachable because of the weakened guard).\n\n**Single planted bug:** line 157 of `SslContextManager.java`, `&&` should be `||`."}],"resolvedModel":"claude-opus-4-8","totalDurationMs":34498,"totalTokens":23234,"totalToolUseCount":3,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1641,"cache_read_input_tokens":20050,"output_tokens":1541,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1641},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1541,"cache_read_input_tokens":20050,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1641,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1641,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"toolStats":{"readCount":2,"searchCount":0,"bashCount":1,"editFileCount":0,"linesAdded":0,"linesRemoved":0,"otherToolCount":0}}}
